description: From in- +‎ numerable; from Middle English innumerable, from Latin innumerābilis, from in- +‎ numerābilis.

adjectives.description: innumerable (comparative more innumerable, superlative most innumerable)

entries.meaning: Not capable of being counted, enumerated, or numbered
examples: The casualties of the Second World War were so great that they are innumerable.

entries.meaning: Of a very high number; extremely numerous
